        description: "Paint vertex colors on a static mesh actor to simulate procedural dirt, moss, edge wear, and water staining. Analyzes each vertex's normal direction and position to determine:\\n  R channel: Dirt/grime in concavities and sheltered areas\\n  G channel: Moss/growth on upward/north-facing surfaces\\n  B channel: Edge wear on convex edges and exposed surfaces\\n  A channel: Water staining below overhangs and drip lines\\n\\nThe source material must use vertex color channels to blend wear textures. This tool only paints the vertex colors — the visual result depends on material setup.",
